



Public Finance (Yusen Sung)





Taxation Theory (Government Revenues)

財 政 學 專 題 (租 稅 理 論)



 1  Instructor: Yusen Sung

 Website: http://homepage.ntu.edu.tw/~ysung/
 Email: ysung@ntu.edu.tw
 Drop-in Open Office Hours: See here


 2  Class Time:

 2:20~5:10pm Monday
 
Classroom etiquette:

 You may enter or leave the classroom at any time, but please do it quietly.
   You may bring food or drinks to the classroom. But, no smelly food.
   Please turn off your cellular phone before the class begins. Rule
 No conversation or phone calls during the exams.
 


 3  Prerequisite:

 Undergraduate-level microeconomics.


 4  Grade Policy:

 There will be an in-class mid-term exam
 and an in-class final exam,
 each accounting for 50% of your final course grade.




 5  Recommended Textbooks:

 1. Public Finance, H.S. Rosen and T. Gayer, 2014(10e), McGraw-Hill. (華泰代理)
 2. Intermediate Public Economics, J. Hindriks and G.D. Myles, 2013(2e), 952pp., MIT Press.




 6  Course Schedule:
(Calendar)


A. Theory:

Introduction: Taxation Theory and Practice
 Positive Analysis: Tax Incidence Note
Positive Analysis: Excess Burden Note
Normative Analysis: Efficiency and Equity Note


Midterm Exam

B. Practice:

Budget Deficit and Government Debt Note
Taiwan
